pr_body:
This should fix #139 

I checked with the old plotting vignette. @GegznaV and @bryanhanson can you please check with the new Rmd version?

The `qplot*()` functions are not yet very capable of mapping other than "pure" columns - but we can leave that to the future **hySpc.ggplot2** package.

[{'comment_id': 440442542, 'comment_body': '- Should `setLabels.select()` and `setLabels.rename()` really be exported?
- since `method.class()` signifies S3 methods, would snake-case names (`setLabels_select()`) be better here?
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 15, 20, 57, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cbeleites', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440443190, 'comment_body': '@eoduniyi, why did you remove the unit tests?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 15, 20, 58, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cbeleites', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440820836, 'comment_body': 'UT2 was:
```R
  # UT2
  test_that("arguments are correctly passed onto mutate/transmute", {
    df <- flu
    df <- dplyr::transmute(df@data, c, c = 0, c = 1)
    expect_equivalent(transmute.hyperSpec(flu, c, c = 0, c = 1), df)
  })
```

But making sure arguments are passed in their correct order is behaviour that is the responsibility of `dplyr` ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 16, 12, 45, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'eoduniyi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440839480, 'comment_body': "Sure, but we still want to check that we get the correct result. pr_body:
`read.txt.Witec.TrueMatch` function works to import Witec ASCII/txt files exported by Witec TrueMatch. One of the key features of this function is the ability to keep extra data from the header information via the `keys_2header` argument:

```R
hy_obj <- read_txt_Witec_TrueMatch(file, "none")
> hy_obj
hyperSpec object
   2 spectra
   2 data columns
   1024 data points / spectrum
wavelength: lambda/nm [numeric] 528.2085 528.3444 ... 664.3265 
data:  (2 rows x 2 columns)
   1. spc:  [matrix, array1024] 683 681 ... 726 
   2. filename: filename [character] /Users/erickoduniyi/Documents/Projects/open-source/hyperspec/hySpc.read.Witec/tests/testthat/Witec_TrueMatch.txt /Users/erickoduniyi/Documents/Projects/open-source/hyperspec/hySpc.read.Witec/tests/testthat/Witec_TrueMatch.txt

hy_obj <- read_txt_Witec_TrueMatch(file, keys_2header = c("Title", "RamanSignal", "FluorescenceSignal"))
> hy_obj
hyperSpec object
   2 spectra
   5 data columns
   1024 data points / spectrum
wavelength: lambda/nm [numeric] 528.2085 528.3444 ... 664.3265 
data:  (2 rows x 5 columns)
   1. spc:  [matrix, array1024] 683 681 ... 726 
   2. Title:  [character] Particle 916 Particle 916 
   3. RamanSignal:  [numeric] 0.4444895 0.4444895 
   4. FluorescenceSignal:  [numeric] 191.4181 191.4181 
   5. filename: filename [character] /Users/erickoduniyi/Documents/Projects/open-source/hyperspec/hySpc.read.Witec/tests/testthat/Witec_TrueMatch.txt /Users/erickoduniyi/Documents/Projects/open-source/hyperspec/hySpc.read.Witec/tests/testthat/Witec_TrueMatch.txt
```

pr_body:
Summary:

I revised the remaining portions of the fileio.Rmd vignette. Overall, it is a beautiful document. 
Super technical. 

I did my best to make it more formal: 

- removing personal pronouns
- reducing wordiness
- correcting misspellings

And when it was clear: 
- punctuation
- syntax 
- semantics

And whatever else my introductory linguistics book taught me.
